Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.43,0:00:04.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Encounters are mysterious!\NBut the world is even more so!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.77,0:00:06.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad I'm with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.94,0:00:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today is a serious code!\NIf adding doesn't work, try subtracting!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.15,0:00:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.90,0:00:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid\Nbut has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.82,0:00:15.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.09,0:01:57.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori, the daughter of\Nthe novelist Shinmei Nintaro,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.88,0:02:02.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,asked the old guy to find\Nher parents who went missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.01,0:02:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They've been missing for two months,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.23,0:02:10.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the publisher still receives\Nhis manuscripts for his new series.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.94,0:02:14.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We went straight to\Nthe publishing company.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.78,0:02:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We found several incomprehensible\Nthings about his manuscripts,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.24,0:02:25.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and they turned out to\Nbe a code calling for help!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.83,0:02:27.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-This is--!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.37,0:02:29.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.96,0:02:33.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a message from\NShinmei-{\i1}sensei {\i0}hidden in these lines!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.63,0:02:40.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which makes it all fit:\Nthat provocative dedication,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.26,0:02:43.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the author's appearance in the story,\Nand the odd lines of dialogue!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.64,0:02:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what is the goal of the person\Nholding him and his wife captive?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.48,0:03:01.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Mystery Writer\NDisappearance Case (Part 2)."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.16,0:03:07.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? Did you\Nrealize something else?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.95,0:03:10.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing much, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.96,0:03:16.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Literature Era{\i0}, Editing Department.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.09,0:03:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the first letters\Nof dialogue are half--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.13,0:03:23.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! You figured out the code?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.72,0:03:24.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.30,0:03:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.01,0:03:30.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A boy speaking Kansai\Ndialect said he figured out the code
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.43,0:03:31.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I should call the police here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.44,0:03:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kansai dialect?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.02,0:03:37.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.40,0:03:42.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon! Don't make me repeat myself,\Nidiot! Just get the cops!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.49,0:03:46.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Hattori-{\i1}kun{\i0}. This is Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.20,0:03:50.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're already there!\NIt's been awhile!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.45,0:03:52.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what's with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.37,0:03:57.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The code. I cracked the\Ncode hidden in "Halves at the Top."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.75,0:04:03.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I pegged him as an angry old man\Nafter I first read his dedication,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.34,0:04:05.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I started to understand as I read
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.84,0:04:11.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that Shinmei-{\i1}han{\i0}'s dialogue\Nin the story was all a code.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.85,0:04:13.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a code?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.48,0:04:19.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... In other words, the dedication\Nwasn't meant to provoke us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.36,0:04:27.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was asking someone to find\Nthe real message hidden in the novel!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.45,0:04:31.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I assume you've deciphered\Nthe coded message then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.54,0:04:36.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... the first part deciphers perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.42,0:04:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The key was the novel's title:\N"Halves of the Top."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.67,0:04:47.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This means the letter at the\Ntop of each line is half of a full letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.84,0:04:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Half of a full letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.14,0:04:53.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reading with that in mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.39,0:04:55.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you get "suke"...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.48,0:04:57.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...then "ke"...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.40,0:04:59.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...then "te"...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.27,0:05:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and at the very end you get a "re."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.07,0:05:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The "ku" and "hoka"\N(other) before it are strange,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.74,0:05:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but if "hoka" is meant to be\Na blank placeholder, you get "ku."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.24,0:05:14.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you read it all together...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.83,0:05:22.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Ta su ke te ku re"...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.00,0:05:22.59,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Tasukete kure (Help us)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.59,0:05:24.80,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Tasukete kure (Help us)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.09,0:05:27.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Help us!" It's an SOS?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.72,0:05:34.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep... My guess is he's being held\Nsomewhere and forced to write.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.43,0:05:38.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... and that's\Nwhy he used this method.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.10,0:05:42.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He could get a message to his\Nreaders without his captor noticing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.77,0:05:47.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My mom was excited because\Nit's the first new story in ten years,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.32,0:05:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so the perp is a crazed fan or\Nsomeone planning to swipe the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.12,0:05:56.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have these manuscripts been paid for yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.46,0:05:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.58,0:06:03.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he'd tell where to send\Nthe money when the story was done.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.71,0:06:06.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Check all suspicious fan letters!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.30,0:06:06.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.13,0:06:10.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but I haven't\Ncracked the entire code yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.09,0:06:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Inspector?! Inspector?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.97,0:06:19.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Inspector! Hey! Where'd\Nyou go?! Quit playing around!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.60,0:06:26.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, Hattori.\NAbout Shinmei-{\i1}sensei{\i0}'s other lines...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.74,0:06:29.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! If it isn't Kudo!\NWhat're you doing there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.65,0:06:32.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing, I just happened to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.07,0:06:35.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I bet! You and me are a lot alike!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.54,0:06:38.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We cross paths before we even know it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.25,0:06:39.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just get back to the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.37,0:06:45.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! You should come to Osaka!\NI'll treat you to some great {\i1}udon{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.46,0:06:48.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stand the\Nheavy flavor in Tokyo!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.80,0:06:49.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.80,0:06:51.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry! Sorry! The code, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.68,0:06:55.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I managed to decipher\Nthe first lines of dialogue,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.01,0:07:00.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but "halves at the top"\Ndoesn't fit with the next ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.52,0:07:02.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Put together, you get...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.60,0:07:12.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Watashi hoka ka i he ima i\Nhaku re no tokoro han hito wa."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.57,0:07:17.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you remove the second\N"hoka," only "watashi" makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.24,0:07:21.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"He" and "ima" are iffy, but they\Ndon't combine into anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.42,0:07:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems we still don't have\Nall the pieces to this code.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.34,0:07:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... there has to be a big piece\Nto this code hidden somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.35,0:07:36.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori? What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.60,0:07:38.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.81,0:07:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're there, why should\NI puzzle over it from so far away?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.73,0:07:46.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the rest's all yours, Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.90,0:07:50.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lemme know if you\Nfigure anything out! Good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.24,0:07:52.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.53,0:07:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! That's right! Hattori-{\i1}kun\N{\i0}should know the rest of the code!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.95,0:07:56.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.41,0:08:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't me! He was the one who--!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.29,0:08:09.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector... this is Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.63,0:08:14.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's forget about the Osaka\Nboy and solve this ourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.82,0:08:17.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Good call!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.26,0:08:19.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, are you feeling sleepy?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.76,0:08:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.10,0:08:27.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know! When you always go,\N"Funya!" or "Hohe!"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.36,0:08:29.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope, nothing yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.77,0:08:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.94,0:08:36.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Help us! Help us!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.45,0:08:38.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Help us!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.49,0:08:41.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad... Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.75,0:08:46.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. I'm sure we'll\Nfind your mother and father.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.96,0:08:48.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.04,0:08:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So let's use our heads, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.34,0:08:52.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.17,0:08:58.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn! Adding or removing\Nnearby letters doesn't do anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.26,0:09:00.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this code?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.64,0:09:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I also don't know who abducted them!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.35,0:09:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be natural to pay close\Nattention to your captive's writings.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.19,0:09:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the captor is a fan,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.27,0:09:17.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he'd clearly be suspicious of that\Natypical dedication and character.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.28,0:09:21.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He would've at least deciphered\Nthe first "help me" by now!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.66,0:09:24.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In which case, he'd be\Nafter the manuscript payment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.83,0:09:27.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that can't be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.42,0:09:31.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wouldn't hold a person\Ncaptive two whole months for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.25,0:09:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't figure out the\Ncaptor's identity or this code!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.38,0:09:38.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Darn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.30,0:09:41.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! This is wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.10,0:09:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Using French to fancy things up\Nis fine, but don't spell stuff wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.81,0:09:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.94,0:09:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,French?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.44,0:09:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Humour" is spelled "h-u-m-o-u-r."\NYou're missing the "h."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.86,0:10:01.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not pronounced, though,\Nso I can understand the mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.70,0:10:08.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! Now I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.88,0:10:14.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In which case, the code is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.21,0:10:16.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can read it! I can read it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.46,0:10:19.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can read every single letter!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.43,0:10:25.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! That's definitely where\NShinmei-{\i1}sensei {\i0}is being held!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.02,0:10:26.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.98,0:10:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinmei-{\i1}sensei {\i0}also has dialogue\Nin the eighth chapter we just got!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.35,0:10:32.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.40,0:10:35.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.20,0:10:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! There's no time!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.62,0:10:48.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't hurry,\Nhe and his wife will be--!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.71,0:10:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! I'll just do like always...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.83,0:10:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and use this Tranquilizer\NWristwatch to knock the old guy out!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.75,0:11:00.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}. Let me introduce you.\NThis is our chief editor...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.76,0:11:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I missed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.69,0:11:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops! I guess I have no choice!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.40,0:11:18.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chief! Chief! What's wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.99,0:11:24.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll just have to have him play a detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.24,0:11:28.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now to set the Voice-Changing\NBowtie to use his voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.37,0:11:30.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.04,0:11:33.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute!\NI don't know what he sounds like!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.21,0:11:35.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.63,0:11:37.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing down there?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.59,0:11:41.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh, just playing Hide-and-Seek!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.80,0:11:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad!\NThere's only one tranquilizer dart!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.01,0:11:51.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have to wait for them\Nto crack the code themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.77,0:11:52.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.94,0:11:57.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't hurry,\NShinmei-{\i1}sensei {\i0}will...!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.40,0:12:02.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened!\NPlease wake up, Chief! Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.15,0:12:07.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's snoring. Almost reminds\Nme of "Sleeping Kogoro."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.16,0:12:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.08,0:12:13.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you laughing about?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.08,0:12:17.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The chief editor is copying how you sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.63,0:12:19.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He seems like he has lots of humor!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.51,0:12:25.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Humor? As always,\Nyou know strange words for a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.68,0:12:29.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those men were talking about it just now!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.18,0:12:33.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were saying\Nstuff about "humour"! Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.60,0:12:34.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.98,0:12:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He misspelled the word,\Nso I fixed it for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.32,0:12:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot to add the "h."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.45,0:12:44.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.16,0:12:47.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But French people sure are strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.87,0:12:51.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They don't read "h" at the start of words!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.83,0:12:55.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they don't say "h,"\Nthey should remove it from the start!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.67,0:12:57.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remove it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.21,0:12:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...from the start?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.92,0:13:05.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That reminds me, Shinmei-{\i1}sensei{\i0}'s\Ncharacter lives in France, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.01,0:13:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.51,0:13:09.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Mori-{\i1}kun..{\i0}. could this be--?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.51,0:13:13.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... the other key to\Nthis code might be the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.52,0:13:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that "h" isn't pronounced\Nat the start of words in French.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.48,0:13:19.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Silent "h" s!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.36,0:13:23.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Characters that start with "h"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.69,0:13:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it mean to remove the\Nh from ha, hi, hu, he, and ho?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.41,0:13:31.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.74,0:13:38.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it means you have to drop the\N"h" letter when combining letters,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.83,0:13:42.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the "hoka" in the first part works.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.42,0:13:50.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Using all of this to decipher\NMr. Shinmei's second scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.35,0:13:53.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you get "watashi"...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.39,0:13:54.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...then "ga"...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.93,0:13:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...then "ima"...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.64,0:13:58.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...then "i"...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.39,0:14:00.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...then "ru"...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.02,0:14:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...then "tokoro"...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.07,0:14:03.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...then "wa"...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.32,0:14:12.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All together, it's "watashi\Nga ima i ru tokoro wa"...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.24,0:14:14.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The place I'm at now"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.25,0:14:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! It makes a sentence!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.91,0:14:22.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. He used that "wa" instead\Nof "ha" because of the "h" rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.42,0:14:29.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! When you decipher\Nthe third scene he's in, you get...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.76,0:14:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Ki to shi te i ho te ru"...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.14,0:14:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kido City Hotel? What hotel is that?\NI've never heard of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.44,0:14:43.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It could be using\NHepburn romanization!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.57,0:14:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In which case, "hu" would be "fu."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.99,0:14:53.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you keep the first "fu,"\Nit would combine to make "hai."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.49,0:14:57.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Haido City Hotel?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.08,0:15:01.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning the fourth set of\Nlines is probably the room number.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.25,0:15:03.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.67,0:15:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"2407 go shitsu"...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.59,0:15:13.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Room 2407"!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.72,0:15:17.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! We go straight to\NHaido City Hotel, Room 2407!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.93,0:15:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.77,0:15:19.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.77,0:15:21.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Takagi-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.56,0:15:24.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this manuscript!\NThere's more dialogue!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.27,0:15:30.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is the eighth chapter\Nthat was just faxed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.86,0:15:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.53,0:15:34.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Haya ku..." (hurry)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.87,0:15:40.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Ji kan ga nai..." (there's no time)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.21,0:15:44.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Hurry, there's no time!"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.21,0:15:51.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.22,0:15:53.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Hurry it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.31,0:16:06.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haido City Hotel.\NFollow those police cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.40,0:16:06.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.98,0:16:07.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.20,0:16:14.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad... Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.91,0:16:19.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! Mom! Please be okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.16,0:16:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.91,0:16:24.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"There's not much time" can also mean
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.46,0:16:27.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that danger is looming but it's not too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.96,0:16:33.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been barely an hour\Nsince that manuscript was sent,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.30,0:16:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and it's still the middle of the novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.59,0:16:37.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a good chance they're alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.30,0:16:39.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.19,0:16:48.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't understand\Nwhat the captor wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.82,0:16:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is a crazed fan anxious for the new\NDet. Samonji series behind this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.24,0:16:56.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.16,0:16:59.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it an abduction to\Nget a popular writer's money?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.03,0:17:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Room 2407 is a suite.\NThat doesn't fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.12,0:17:08.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what is the captor after?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.67,0:17:14.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is the plan of the person\Nwho's forcing Shinmei-{\i1}sensei {\i0}to write
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.47,0:17:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even when he can't sign his own name?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.43,0:17:20.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute!\NIf he can't sign his name...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.35,0:17:25.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that means he's dictating\Nhis story to someone!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.48,0:17:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then he's having\Nsomeone else type it all out,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.48,0:17:32.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even when one misplaced\Nletter could ruin the code?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.65,0:17:35.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.28,0:17:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Adding and removing for no\Nreason would make anyone suspicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.83,0:17:46.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if his wife was typing,\Nthe person watching would notice!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.75,0:17:55.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Hold on! Could\Nthis incident actually be--?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.77,0:18:08.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Room 2407... Alright! This is the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.85,0:18:13.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The captor may have\Na weapon! Everyone stay sharp!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.70,0:18:27.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.33,0:18:29.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.75,0:18:31.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori! Why are you here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.21,0:18:34.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get back, Madam!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.55,0:18:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Freeze! Police!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.60,0:18:51.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.48,0:18:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.86,0:18:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father passed\Naway just moments ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.45,0:19:01.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.53,0:19:06.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I called your home many times,\Nbut I couldn't get a hold of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.71,0:19:14.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're the one\Nwho abducted Mr. Shinmei?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.09,0:19:15.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.05,0:19:19.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's my husband's personal physician.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.63,0:19:22.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then who's the kidnapper?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.93,0:19:30.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no kidnapper.\NIf there was, it'd be Shinmei himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.69,0:19:32.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean the code was--?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.77,0:19:33.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't mean--!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.02,0:19:37.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A fabrication put together by my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.98,0:19:40.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.65,0:19:45.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband was always saying this...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.32,0:19:52.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I, of course, feel happiness\Nwhen I receive praise for my works,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.79,0:19:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but in my forty years of writing,\Nthere's a happiness I've yet to have.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.34,0:20:01.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just once, I'd like to\Nsee with my own eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.59,0:20:10.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the face of a reader who solves\Na mystery before I give the solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.47,0:20:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said he wanted\Nto do so before he died,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.56,0:20:21.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so his physician and\NI helped him write his story here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.44,0:20:22.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before dying?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.57,0:20:28.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He lost use of his arms two\Nweeks ago, due to terminal cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.58,0:20:31.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why his signatures were copies?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.71,0:20:35.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for worrying you, Kaori.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.38,0:20:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father told me not to tell you,\Nto give believability to his code.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.92,0:20:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive your father, and consider\Nit his last selfish act, Kaori...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.78,0:22:29.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about your false alarms...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.78,0:22:35.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Surely he knew a code like that\Ncould've caused a big police panic!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.66,0:22:40.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he always wrote at the end of his novels
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.71,0:22:44.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that he wanted to see the proud\Nlook of one of his readers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.75,0:22:48.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was probably waiting for a\Nreader who figured everything out
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.72,0:22:51.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to show up and say, "I solved it!"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.55,0:22:55.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But no one ever came.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.18,0:23:00.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now that he's gone,\Nthe novel will stay unfinished.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.69,0:23:02.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let that happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.11,0:23:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll write the rest of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.82,0:23:08.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't shame the name Shinmei Nintaro!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.53,0:23:17.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two months after this incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.16,0:23:21.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori-{\i1}san {\i0}spectacularly\Ncompleted her father's novel
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.50,0:23:26.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and "Halves at the Top"\Nmanaged to become a bestseller!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.96,0:23:31.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, a TV version was\Nsoon made and earned great reviews,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.80,0:23:35.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which led her to enter the writing world!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.76,0:23:41.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although this was because\Nshe was as skilled as her father,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.39,0:23:47.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the dimwitted detective, tomboy girl,\Nand the cheeky boy in glasses
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.40,0:23:52.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who assisted Samonji in the\Nlast half of the story also helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.07,0:23:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't say who they were based on...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.20,0:23:59.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but I could do\Nwithout the "cheeky" part.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.00,0:24:03.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just a regular Tokyo--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.75,0:24:09.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.34,0:24:13.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get a bad feeling that\Nthe killer is playing with us...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.79,0:24:16.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bad feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.43,0:24:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.99,0:24:28.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan special--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.14,0:24:30.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Naniwa Serial Murder Case."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.14,0:24:49.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's special hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.95,0:24:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rearview mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.83,0:24:53.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode is a one-hour special.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.48,0:24:55.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan goes to Osaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.05,0:24:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
